In your R Markdown document, find the derivative expression and slope at the indicated value for each the following functions in R (each in a separate code chunk).

f(x)=x^2 at x=3 P(a)=2(3a+2)^45 at a=1.2 g(t)=4t(t2+1)3 at t=0

f_x <- expression(x ^ 2 )
P_a <- expression(2 *(3 * a + 2) ^ 4 - 5)
g_t <- expression(-4 * t * (t ^ 2 + 1) ^ 3)

df_dx <- D(f_x, "x")
dP_da <- D(P_a, 'a')
dg_dt <- D(g_t, "t")

Section 4: Make a penguin plot In a new code chunk, create a ggplot graph of penguin bill length versus bill depth (using the penguins dataset in the palmerpenguins package), with point color dependent on species. You should attach the tidyverse and palmerpenguins package in your .Rmd setup chunk. Update labels and add a title.

ggplot(data = penguins, aes(x = bill_depth_mm, y = bill_length_mm)) + 
         geom_point(aes(color = species)) +
                      labs(x = "Bill Length (mm)",
                           y = "Bill Depth (mm)",
                           title = "Palmer Penguins")
